# Kibo UI Components

We use Kibo UI (https://kibo-ui.com) - a modern React component library built on top of shadcn/ui.
Kibo UI provides composable, accessible, and open-source components designed to work seamlessly with shadcn/ui.

## Prerequisites

- Node.js (version 18 or later)
- React project (version 18 or later)
- shadcn/ui installed

## Installation & Updates

Add new components: `npx kibo-ui add {component-name}`
Update existing components: `npx kibo-ui update {component-name}`

**Note**: Components are installed to `app/components/kibo-ui/` to align with the project structure.

## Import Patterns

**IMPORTANT**: All Kibo UI components are added directly to your codebase and can be imported from their local paths using the `~/components/kibo-ui/` alias.

Example:

```typescript
import { Announcement } from "~/components/kibo-ui/announcement";
```

